Package: fishblicc
Title: Bayesian Length Interval Catch Curve
Version: 0.9.9
Authors@R: 
    person("Paul A.H.", "Medley", , "paulahmedley@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The package provides functions for fitting a catch curve to
    length frequency data. The model assumes that the fish population is
    in a steady state (constant recruitment), individual fish growth
    (Linf) is Gamma distributed with a fixed CV and mean following the von
    Bertalanffy function, and mortality is constant within each length
    interval (bin). The model provides the expected frequency in each
    length interval for a negative binomial likelihood. The model can fit
    to multiple length frequencies each with different selectivities made
    up of logistic / normal mixtures representing different fishing gears
    applied over different time periods.  The model is fitted using Stan.
